Saudi Arabia (SABIC) â€™s  Tadawul All Share
Index (SASEIDX)  fell for a fourth day, dropping 0.3 percent at the 3:30
p.m. close in Riyadh. The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  fell 0.7 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Alinma Bank (ALINMA)   slumped 2.5 percent, the biggest
decrease since March 21, to 15.55 riyals. First-quarter profit
at the Islamic lender rose to 150 million riyals ($40 million)
from 70 million riyals a year earlier. That fell short of a 207
million-riyal estimate at  Beltone Financial (BTFH) , according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  Saudi Ceramic (SCERCO)   advanced for the fifth time in
six days, rising 1.8 percent to 158.75 riyals. The manufacturer
and retailer of ceramic products said it plans a capital
increase by distributing free shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
